	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64448360"><p>&gt; I am not sure why using nuclear warheads to take them out is inherently worse than shooting them down with conventional weapons.</p><p>I tend to agree.  Conventional weaponry still gives you Kessler's Syndrome, and in space you're not typically worried about fallout or pressure waves.  The advantage of a nuke might be to clear out a large volume of an orbit quickly, but then again there's a LOT of distance between things out there.</p><p>But I think maybe you're underestimating the utility of space as a platform fro<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64448360">

